description:
Entry Level , Experienced direct to home & Leadership in Solar Marketing and Sales Representative

**Book a one on one interview :**

https://calendar.app.google/SyYV9YNxhoj5y5tt6

ABOUT OUR COMPANY

Awarded the largest residential solar company in the US, we are set to become the largest energy provider in the United States over the next 15 years. You will be joining a fast-paced, dynamic organization focused on changing how the world uses energy.

ABOUT THE OPPORTUNITY

We are seeking talented candidates who are passionate about innovation, clean energy and delivering the best possible service to our customers. We are seeking highly motivated and reliable candidates seeking an entry-level opportunity into one of America's premier sales and clean energy companies.

This personal-development program is designed to give top candidates an opportunity to grow their communication and sales skills, industry knowledge and familiarity with our company while making top dollar for their efforts. This includes a 40-hour work week, top benefits, paid vacation and a culture of rewarding top performers.

This entry-level program is typically a 6 month stepping stone to a high-potential sales position, where top performers earn over two-hundred thousand dollars per year within our company. This includes paid training and personal attention as you begin or extend your career in sales. Successful people in this program are our first stop for filling open positions in management, recruiting, inside sales, field sales and internal support.

Primary Duties: Working closely with a team that meets on a daily basis and is given the latest in technology to be able to scout residential neighborhoods for prospective customers. These prospective customers could qualify for money-saving solar energy packages which can include installation of the solar energy system free of charge. The Solar Marketing and Sales Representative will introduce prospective customers to Trinity Solar and work with them to set up informational appointments.

COMPENSATION

* Discussed upon interview.

RESPONSIBILITIES

* Generate qualified leads of homeowners interested in residential solar energy systems;
* Serve as a consultant and provide useful product knowledge to qualifying homeowners;
* Acquire, retain and constantly develop industry knowledge;
* Meet and exceed lead generation goals.

DESIRED EXPERIENCE AND QUALIFICATIONS

* 1+ years of sales, customer service and/or consulting experience;
* Must have excellent communication and customer service skills;
* Must be self-driven & highly motivated;
* Ability to work under pressure to meet deadlines and quotas;
* Must be flexible working weekend and evening hours;
* Ability to prioritize and multitask appropriately;
* Must have reliable transportation;
* Certain opportunities require a clean DMV record;
* Must be able to pass a pre-employment background check;
* Must have cell phone with data and internet;
* Applicants must be 18 years old or older; and,
* Bilingual abilities are a plus.

Job Types: Full-time, Contract

Pay: $65,000.00 - $110,000.00 per year

Work Location: On the road
